<TITLE> Ugandan vice president in city </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 7 (bdnews24.com)Ugandan vice president Gilbert Bukenya arrived in the capital on Thursday on a six-day visit to witness the empowerment of the poor by BRAC, world's one of the largest NGOs. Bukenya was scheduled to meet with president Zillur Rahman in the evening. The Ugandan high commissioner posted in New Delhi, foreign ministry and BRAC officials welcomed him at the Zia International Airport in the morning. A press release of BRAC said Bukenya will visit a number of its programmes in Savar, Manikganj and Gazipur. He will also see field-level activities of the NGO, including microcredit, remittance, community development, education, health, water and sanitation programmes in Dhamrai, Sripur in Gazipur and Savar, the release said. On Monday evening, the visiting vice president will see BRAC chairperson Fazle Hasan Abed. BRAC began its operations in Uganda in 2006.
